SIMPLE: oddly
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Oddly
<hw>Odd"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In an odd manner;
unevenly.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>In a peculiar manner; strangely; queerly;
curiously.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A figure a little more <xex>oddly</xex>
turned.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Locke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A great black substance, . . . very <qex>oddly</qex> shaped.</q>
<rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Math.)</fld> <def>In a manner measured by an odd
number.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oddment</ent>⟦br⟧
